data.chText: 推行，采用（规章制度）；强制实行
data.enText: to introduce a new law, rule, tax, etc.; to order that a rule, punishment, etc. be used

data.chText: 当局开始对燃油征收一项新税。
data.enText: A new tax was imposed on fuel.
to force sb/sth to have to deal with sth that is difficult or unpleasant

data.chText: 强行限制 / 管制 / 约束某事物
这个制度给很多人增加了额外的经济负担。
data.enText: This system imposes additional financial burdens on many people.

data.chText: 使（别人）接受自己的意见
data.enText: to make sb accept the same opinions, wishes etc. as your own

data.chText: 她并不想勉强家人接受自己的价值观。
data.enText: She didn't want to impose her values on her family.

data.chText: 显而易见，有少数几个人设法把自己的意志强加于别人。
data.enText: It was noticeable how a few people managed to impose their will on the others.

data.chText: 勉强（某人做某事）；硬要…和…在一起
data.enText: to expect sb to do sth for you or to spend time with you, when it may not be convenient for them

data.chText: “你一定得留下吃午饭。”“唔，谢谢，但我不想添麻烦…”
data.enText: ‘You must stay for lunch.’ ‘Well, thanks, but I don't want to impose…’

data.chText: 大家都欺负戴夫脾气好。
data.enText: Everyone imposes on Dave's good nature.

data.chText: 使接受，使意识到（自己的在场或想法）
data.enText: to make sb/sth accept or be aware of your presence or ideas

data.chText: 欧洲文明是最先传扬到全世界的。
data.enText: European civilization was the first to impose itself across the whole world.

simple_means.memory_skill: im 使…；加以…；饰以… + pos 放 + e → 强行放置 → 把…强加于

means: 使(别人)接受自己的意见

example: The principal visited his rage on the students

tr: compel to behave in a certain way

value.def: If you impose something on people, you use your authority to force them to accept it.

example.ex: Britain imposed fines on airlines which bring in passengers without proper papers...
example.tran: 英国会对运载证件不齐全的乘客进入国内的航空公司课以罚款。

example.ex: Many companies have imposed a pay freeze...
example.tran: 许多公司已经强制冻结了工资。

example.ex: The conditions imposed on volunteers were stringent.
example.tran: 对志愿者的限定条件非常严格。

example.ex: ...the imposition of a ban on cycling in the city centre.
example.tran: 强制实行不许在市中心骑自行车的禁令

value.def: If you impose your opinions or beliefs on other people, you try and make people accept them as a rule or as a model to copy.

example.ex: Parents of either sex should beware of imposing their own tastes on their children.
example.tran: 父母双方都应切记不要把自己的喜好强加给孩子。

value.def: If something imposes strain, pressure, or suffering on someone, it causes them to experience it.

example.ex: The filming imposed an additional strain on her.
example.tran: 拍摄任务使她承受了格外大的压力。

example.ex: ...the pressures imposed upon teachers by ceaseless curriculum reforms.
example.tran: 无休止的课程改革使教师承受的压力

value.tran: 使遭受，使承受(压力、痛苦等)

value.def: If someone imposes on you, they unreasonably expect you to do something for them which you do not want to do.

example.ex: I was afraid you'd simply feel we were imposing on you...
example.tran: 我担心你会觉得我们是在勉强你。

example.ex: 'Mum thinks I should stop imposing on your hospitality, Leo,' said Grace.
example.tran: “利奥,我妈妈觉得我不应该再在这儿麻烦你了，”格雷丝说。

value.tran: 把…硬加给;把…强塞给;勉强(某人)做事

example.ex: I know this is an imposition. But please hear me out.
example.tran: 我知道这是强人所难。但是请听我说完。

value.def: If someone imposes themselves on you, they force you to accept their company although you may not want to.

example.ex: I didn't want to impose myself on my married friends.
example.tran: 我不想打扰自己已婚的朋友。
